<define-tag description>security update</define-tag>
<define-tag moreinfo>
<p>Patrick Coleman discovered that missing input sanitising in the ADPCM
decoder of the VLC media player may result in the execution of arbitrary
code if a malformed media file is opened.</p>

<p>For the stable distribution (jessie), this problem has been fixed in
version 2.2.4-1~deb8u1.</p>

<p>For the unstable distribution (sid), this problem has been fixed in
version 2.2.4-1.</p>

<p>We recommend that you upgrade your vlc packages.</p>
</define-tag>

